How to use the `git filter-branch` command
=============================================

The `git filter-branch` command is a powerful tool that allows you to modify the history of a Git repository. It can be used to re-write the commit history of a repository, or to create a new branch that is a modified version of an existing branch. In this guide, we will go over the basics of how to use the `git filter-branch` command, including some common use cases and examples.

### What is `git filter-branch`?

