 How to use the `git filter-branch` command?
=============================================

The `git filter-branch` command is a powerful tool that allows you to modify the history of a Git repository. It can be used to re-write the commit history, squash commits, or even remove commits entirely. In this guide, we will go over the basics of how to use the `git filter-branch` command, as well as some advanced techniques for using it effectively.

Understanding the Basics of `git filter-branch`
